<SECOND>PM-People-Kasem,0199</SECOND>
<HEAD>Casey and Jean Kasem Play Host for Homeless Benefit</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Casey Kasem and his actress-wife, Jean,
transformed their luxurious home into a huge lawn circus to raise
money for the homeless.
   Celebrities including Stevie Wonder, Paula Abdul, Lou Ferrigno,
Ally Sheedy, Cesar Romero, Valerie Harper, and Victoria Principal
were among the more than 2,000 guests, said Karen Kukurin, a
spokeswoman for the couple.
   Jugglers, mimes, sword swallowers, clowns, and fire eaters
performed along the 3-acre estate's nine-hole golf course,
transformed into a midway for Sunday's event, she said.
   The fund-raiser also featured an auction of $3.5 million worth
of sculpture and oil paintings.
   It was not immediately known how much the auction had raised for
an Oct. 7 march on Washington, D.C., to draw attention to the
problem on homelessness, said Kukurin.
   The Kasems are among about 200 celebrities planning to attend
the march.
   ``The affordable housing crisis and its most visible symptom _
homelessness _ are a national disgrace,'' said Jean Kasem, whose
acting credits include the television series ``Cheers'' and ``The
Tortellis.''
   Casey Kasem's syndicated radio show is heard 450 stations each
week.
