   ``The recommendation to cease publication of The Raleigh Times
was one that was accepted reluctantly, but it was not unexpected,''
he said. ``For several years, we have watched as afternoon dailies
in metropolitan areas closed.''
   Daniels said most of the task force recommendations ``were
directed toward making The News and Observer a better and more
complete newspaper.'' Many of those improvements could not be made
as long as the Times was being published.
</TEXT>
