Hills police officer Paul Kramer during a traffic stop, of driving
without a valid driver's license and of having an open container of
alcohol in her car.
   Miss Gabor was acquitted of disobeying Kramer by driving away as
he checked her motor vehicle record on June 14. She faces up to 18
months, five days in jail and a $3,500 fine at her Oct. 17
sentencing.
   ``What did I do that was so wrong?'' Miss Gabor said today,
repeating the points she raised at her trial. ``I protected myself
from a 6-foot-4 man who called me every name in the world and who
treated me like ... a streetwalker. I should go for that to jail? I
think that would be really _ that would be silly.''
