<FIRST>r a PM-People-CosbyDaughter 1stLd-Writethru a0581 10-02 0399</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-People-Cosby Daughter, 1st Ld - Writethru, a0581,0402</SECOND>
<HEAD>Cosby Daughter Treated for Drug, Alcohol Habit</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: SUBS penultimate graf with 3 grafs to UPDATE with further from
Cosby spokesman. Picks up last graf.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LANTANA, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Entertainer Bill Cosby used the ``tough
love'' approach with his 23-year-old daughter, Erinn, when she told
him that she was addicted to drugs and alcohol, both father and
daughter say.
   Erinn Cosby, who checked out of a drug rehabilitation center
Sept. 24, said she began using cocaine at age 19, but that her
parents had no idea se had a drug habit until she wrote them a
letter six months ago. She said she had kicked a $200-a-day cocaine
habit by then but was still heavily hooked on pot and alcohol.
   Cosby, who plays a father-knows-best-style dad on his hit
television series and wrote a best-seller ``Fatherhood'' about his
experiences with his five children, said he consulted specialists
on how to handle the situation and he and his wife wrote back
urging her to seek treatment. But they refused to coddle her.
   ```Tough love' is the only way of dealing with this. We love her
and want her to get better, but we have to take a very firm, very
tough stand that forces her to realize that no one can fix things
for her,'' the star told the National Enquirer. ``She has to beat
this on her own.''
   ``People see Bill Cosby as a super dad. But I'm proof that drug
and alcohol tragedies can happen even in the most loving
families,'' said his daughter, who is staying with a cousin in
Boston after her five-week stay at Edgehill Newport hospital in
Rhode Island.
   David Brokaw, Cosby's Los Angeles-based spokesman, confirmed
today that Ms. Cosby is under treatment for a drug and alcohol
problem, and said Cosby would have no further comment other than
what he had told the Enquirer.
   The Enquirer piece is ``the only interview that he's been
willing to give on the matter,'' Brokaw said. ``He has a
relationship with them. He has found them to treat him fairly.''
   He said he couldn't confirm any of what Ms. Cosby is quoted as
saying except that she did have a substance abuse problem.
   Ms. Cosby, the second of Cosby's five children, told the
Lantana-based newspaper she began drinking and smoking marijuana
about age 14 while at boarding school.
</TEXT>
