<FIRST>r i AM-Argentina-Drownings     10-02 0161</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Argentina-Drownings,0167</SECOND>
<HEAD>Ferry Capsizes, At Least 5 Dead</HEAD>
<DATELINE>POSADAS, Argentina (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A ferry traveling between Argentina
and Brazil capsized while crossing the turbulent Uruguay River on
Monday and five people drowned, officials reported. Up to 10 people
were reported missing.
   The Santa Victoria, a 26-foot launch with a crew of three, was
overloaded with 30 passengers, according to the coast guard. It
said a passing barge rescued the survivors, and five bodies were
recovered.
   The coast guard said at least four people were missing, but
border police reported nine or 10 people were not accounted for.
   Initial reports indicated the barge, transporting a bus and
several cars, collided with the ferry. But the independent news
agency Diarios y Noticias reported later that there was no
collision.
   No reason for the accident was given. However, the news agency
said the ferry was designed to carry only 12 people.
   It capsized shortly after it left Panambi, Argentina, for Vera
Cruz, Brazil.
