<HEAD>Channel Tunnel Costs Soar, Anglo-French Developers Say</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The estimated cost of building the English Channel
tunnel has jumped to $11.20 billion from $7.80 billion two years
ago, developers Eurotunnel PLC said Monday.
   The builders and banks for the 31-mile underwater rail link
between Britain and France say the price tag is likely to go higher.
   Eurotunnel, the Anglo-French consortium, said it will probably
turn to shareholders and its creditor bankers to raise extra money
