<FIRST>d f BC-CoalProdn     10-02 0097</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Coal Prodn,0101</SECOND>
<HEAD>Coal Output Up</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic coal production totaled 19.9 million
short tons during the week ended Sept. 23, up slightly from the
19.6 million short tons produced the previous week, the Department
of Energy reported Monday.
   The U.S. coal industry produced 19.3 million short tons in the
same week last year, according to the department's Energy
Information Administration.
   Domestic coal production so far this year is 699.9 million short
tons, 5.9 percent above last year's production at this time, the
agency said.
   The week's production accounts for bituminous and lignite coal.
</TEXT>
