<SECOND>AM-France-Arms,0110</SECOND>
<HEAD>French Arms Exports Rose 30 Percent in 1988</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PARIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The value of export orders booked by French arms
manufacturers surged by 30 percent last year to $6 billion, the
French Defense Ministry said Monday.
   The ministry said 53 percent of the total was accounted for by
orders for aeronautical equipment and 36 percent for land-based
defense equipment, while naval orders represented 11 percent.
   France's biggest customers remain the Middle East and North
Africa, together accounting for 55 percent of total orders. North
America and Western Europe account for 24 percent of the 1988
total, and South America for 14 percent.
